# Grok Build Environment Configuration
#
# DigitalOcean Serverless Inference (recommended):
#   MODEL_ACCESS_KEY  Model access key (Inference > Manage
#                        in the DigitalOcean control panel)
#   DO_INFERENCE_MODEL   Default model alias from /root/.grok/config.toml, e.g.
#                        gpt-5-5 (default), gpt-5-3-codex, claude-opus-4-8,
#                        deepseek-v4-pro, kimi-k2-6, qwen3-coder-flash
#   DO_INFERENCE_ROUTER  Optional. Name of a DigitalOcean Intelligent Inference
#                        Router attached to MODEL_ACCESS_KEY (in the control
#                        panel). If set, requests route through "router:<name>"
#                        using the SAME key and the router becomes the default.
#
# xAI account (alternative): leave MODEL_ACCESS_KEY empty and either run
#   `grok login --device-auth` on the droplet, or set an xAI API key:
#   XAI_API_KEY      xAI API key (xai-...) from https://console.x.ai
#
# On first boot, 001_onboot reads /etc/environment first, then this file.
# If MODEL_ACCESS_KEY (or XAI_API_KEY) is set in either place, Grok Build is
# configured automatically and the interactive setup wizard is skipped.
# Otherwise run the wizard on first SSH login: /opt/setup-grok-build.sh

MODEL_ACCESS_KEY=
DO_INFERENCE_MODEL=gpt-5-5
DO_INFERENCE_ROUTER=
XAI_API_KEY=
